1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,640
You're accusing my dad. There's no proof!

2
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,720
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:38,240
-<i>He must know we're dealing drugs.</i>
-<i>We can't let him live, Kitti.</i>

4
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,560
<i>I'll take care of it myself.</i>

5
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,400
<i>How are you going to handle it?</i>

6
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:50,000
-Sonrak!
-Hurry up!

7
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,800
-Let me go! Sonrak!
-Take him!

8
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:55,240
Go up on stage and sing this.

9
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,800
And you'll see your mother.

10
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:05,040
<i>Oh, my heart</i>

11
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:11,360
<i>Why can't you stay composed?</i>

12
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:14,720
Finally, I'd like to say

13
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:17,680
I now have a dad and a mom!

14
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:26,160
PUNA & SONRAK, TARAGRAND HOTEL

15
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,080
Clear the area.

16
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,960
-Chit!
-Move, quick!

17
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,480
Yes!

18
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:51,600
-Chart, Chit, thanks a lot!
-Yeah.

19
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,120
Thank you, Chart.

20
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,000
Hand me the keys.

21
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:04,880
Step aside, Captain.

22
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,360
Don't go yet, sir.

23
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:09,600
The evidence in this case
points straight at you.

24
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,720
If you're leaving,

25
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:14,280
please check your tires first.

26
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:20,920
Flat tires.
If you want to leave, go ahead.

27
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,720
Manat, you! Handle him!

28
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,320
Let's go.

29
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:37,000
You're not getting away, Superintendent.

30
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,520
Tell them to step aside now.

31
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,760
Are you backing off or not?

32
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:44,640
I can't order them.

33
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,360
They're on duty.

34
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:50,200
Surrender, sir.

35
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:54,520
There's no way
I'll let you and Sergeant Biew escape.

36
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:57,200
If you've done wrong, you have to pay.

37
00:04:57,280 --> 00:05:01,040
No matter how high your rank is,
I won't let you go.

38
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:02,960
Three on three, shall we settle this?

39
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,600
Get down!

40
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,880
I give up. I surrender!

41
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:21,160
You're not getting away,
Superintendent Samuejai.

42
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:24,120
A corrupt cop like you belongs in jail.

43
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,680
Don't rush to die!

44
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:28,440
-Take him in!
-Yes, sir.

45
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,800
Thank you so much, Deputy Chief.

46
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:39,160
The 14K gang stormed the safe house

47
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,840
and a clash broke out.

48
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,280
Kitti got captured in the process.

49
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,360
Deputy Chief.

50
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:49,280
I just got a report
that Chit went to rescue Tod and Wong,

51
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,000
and he's escaping with his men.

52
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,560
-Manat, check the checkpoint.
-Yes, sir.

53
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:57,360
Chaiya, go watch over Singha.
Where's the car holding him?

54
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,680
About to leave the venue.

55
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:01,120
Tell them to stop. Don't let them go yet.

56
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:04,200
Got it. I'll handle it.
Let's split up here.

57
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,200
Yes, sir. Understood.

58
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:18,720
-What's happening, Corporal?
-We can't move. There's a clash ahead.

59
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,160
My men are here to help, huh?

60
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:24,480
Let me go! I'm going to see my son!
Let go!

61
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,080
Take cover! Hey!

62
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:43,080
Last time, you shot me.

63
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:45,400
This time, I'm getting my revenge!

64
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:47,600
Tod.

65
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,120
-Awesome, Chart!
-Let's go.

66
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,800
Pleaw, you bastard!

67
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,520
-You're dead! Hey!
-Wait, don't!

68
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,920
Hey! Tod!

69
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:11,080
Kill them all!

70
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:13,960
Wong!

71
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:18,120
Wong! Wong.

72
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,240
Wong!

73
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,160
Damn it!

74
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,800
Pleaw!

75
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,200
CHECKPOINT

76
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:34,680
Chit.

77
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:42,520
Today

78
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:45,160
is your last day!

79
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Look at me.

80
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:43,240
-Let go!
-Don't worry.

81
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:46,840
My people are taking
your son to the hospital.

82
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,600
The driver just called,

83
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:50,800
they're on the way, almost there.

84
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,920
Kamnan, I've been framed!

85
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:59,440
You still have the nerve
to say you were framed?

86
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:00,760
You have to believe me.

87
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,800
Boss Nok!

88
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:06,160
He's jealous of our label
getting all the big gigs.

89
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,840
He couldn't get them, so that's why

90
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:12,680
he's trying to frame me.
Kamnan, you have to believe me.

91
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,160
At this point,

92
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:18,400
Mr. Singha, I think
you'd better admit your wrongdoing.

93
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,800
Stay out of this!

94
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,320
I want to thank you,

95
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:28,000
Captain Chaiya, and your team

96
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:31,320
for risking yourselves to come here

97
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:34,320
and taking down the drug gang

98
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:36,400
corrupting the youth in Khok Ta Yu.

99
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:38,480
Yes.

100
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:41,760
Kamnan! Don't tell me…

101
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,200
You were working with them?!

102
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,280
I've known about it for a while.

103
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:56,200
How could you do this to me?!

104
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:02,560
How dare you speak to me like that?

105
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:06,000
You dared to sell drugs in Khok Ta Yu

106
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,680
and poison the youth!

107
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,360
And worst of all,

108
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:13,960
you had the nerve
to use my factory as a drug lab!

109
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:18,280
Do you know how much
the parents are suffering

110
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:22,280
seeing their child addicted to drugs?
You're pure evil!

111
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,160
Most importantly,

112
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:39,400
I'm gonna remind you
what kind of evil you are.

113
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:43,360
You tried to kill Onanong

114
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,920
and Phupha, then framed them.

115
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:50,880
Do you know

116
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,200
they've suffered

117
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:56,480
for nearly 20 years?!

118
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,680
I'll ask you again.

119
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,120
I gave you the company to manage,

120
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:08,520
to build your wealth

121
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:12,120
and your security.
Why didn't you do the right thing?!

122
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:15,600
That's my business! Stay out of it!

123
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,800
What were you thinking?

124
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:22,320
Do you realize you've destroyed
your son, Sonrak's future?

125
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:25,280
You've ruined all that your son has built!

126
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:29,480
Hey! Look at me!

127
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:31,120
Look at me!

128
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:37,280
Your son must be so confused.
Sonrak must be wondering

129
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,600
how his father

130
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,920
brought him to this point!

131
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,000
Do you understand?

132
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,160
Sonrak.

133
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:53,080
My son was shot.

134
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:56,000
Sonrak was shot.

135
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:59,280
How is he? How is Sonrak?

136
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:01,000
How is Sonrak?!

137
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:06,760
Sonrak.

138
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:08,640
Yes?

139
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,080
I'm sorry.

140
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,000
Sure.

141
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,680
Mr. Sonrak is safe now.

142
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:22,600
But he's very agitated.
The doctor only allowed him to call.

143
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:24,800
He wants to talk to you.

144
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,480
I want to speak with my son.

145
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:31,040
I want to talk to Sonrak.
Come on. I want to talk.

146
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:34,800
Hello, Dad.

147
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:38,760
Dad, where are you?

148
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,000
Can you turn on the camera?

149
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,240
I want to see your face.

150
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,200
How are you?

151
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:50,920
I'm sorry.

152
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,960
Sonrak, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

153
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:57,480
Dad.

154
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:01,800
<i>Why did you do this to me?</i>

155
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:04,160
Why did you lie to me?

156
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:08,360
You must hate me so much, don't you?

157
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:10,960
I trusted only you.

158
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,280
And you lied to me.

159
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:20,440
<i>From now on, who can I trust?</i>

160
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:25,440
Not only have you destroyed
your own reputation,

161
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:27,880
you've ruined mine too!

162
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:30,200
Why? Why would you do this?!

163
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:32,400
Can you forgive me?

164
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,960
<i>My own father betrayed me, lied to me,</i>
<i>and stabbed me in the back like this.</i>

165
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:39,240
Can you forgive me?

166
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:53,840
Please forgive me.

167
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,000
Get down!

168
00:14:01,680 --> 00:14:03,840
-Mr. Singha!
-Singha! Singha!

169
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:07,400
-Kamnan, please cover this side!
-Singha!

170
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,840
Singha!

171
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:15,120
Singha!

172
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,280
Drop your weapon! Surrender now!

173
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,000
Go.

174
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:14,440
Stop!

175
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:15,960
Put your gun down!

176
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:18,560
Quick!

177
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:15,880
Get down!

178
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:09,040
It's finally over.

179
00:18:14,360 --> 00:18:16,280
"Last order.

180
00:18:16,360 --> 00:18:18,320
Eliminate Captain Chaiya."

181
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:31,720
Chart!

182
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:36,760
Phupha! You're tough to kill, huh?

183
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:23,720
Put your gun down, Chart.

184
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:33,000
No!

185
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:06,480
Please go ahead, Officer.

186
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:18,320
I can't arrest you. By law,

187
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:20,960
I'm still a fugitive myself.

188
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,120
Well then, thank you very much.

189
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:31,880
No problem. I'm glad to help.

190
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,240
You'd better hurry.

191
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:41,560
Father.

192
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,040
RESTROOM

193
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:24,320
-Chaiya! We've got a problem!
-What is it, Teacher?

194
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,520
-Puna's gone missing!
-Huh?

195
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,080
Look, the watch dropped.

196
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,480
Something must have happened.

197
00:21:32,120 --> 00:21:33,080
Puna.

198
00:21:38,320 --> 00:21:40,920
<i>Bring 50 million USD in cash</i>

199
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,600
<i>and your life</i>
<i>in exchange for your loved one.</i>

200
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:47,600
<i>Tonight, I'll wait</i>
<i>at the abandoned forest gas station.</i>

201
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:50,080
<i>I repeat, only you can come.</i>

202
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:53,240
<i>If it's anyone else, she's dead.</i>

203
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:55,840
Chaiya, what happened?

204
00:21:57,720 --> 00:22:00,400
-They've taken my heart, Teacher.
-Huh?

205
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:19,680
Do you really believe

206
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,920
that fool Chaiya

207
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,560
will trade his life for yours?

208
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:30,680
If I had a choice,
I wouldn't want him to come.

209
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:40,440
Playing the heroine for love, huh?

210
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:42,400
You'll see!

211
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:46,960
Chaiya's going to be dead today.

212
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:56,600
I'm here.

213
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:01,320
Chaiya.

214
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:06,280
Are you brave or just crazy,

215
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:07,960
giving up your life

216
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:10,280
for this woman?

217
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:13,760
Don't talk so much. I came to die for her.

218
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,520
Fine, hero.

219
00:23:20,520 --> 00:23:21,360
Then,

220
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:24,600
let's finish this.

221
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:27,600
Put the money over there.

222
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,800
Now.

223
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,320
Open it.

224
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:44,240
Wait.

225
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:47,280
Your gun too.

226
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:50,200
I said, put it down!

227
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:00,520
Good.

228
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,560
Step back.

229
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,040
And don't try any tricks.

230
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:12,080
Hey.

231
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:15,200
You do know that a single spark

232
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:18,280
is a perfect ignition source, right?

233
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:37,920
-Let the woman go.
-Fine.

234
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:39,880
If that's what you want.

235
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:41,640
I said, let the woman go!

236
00:24:46,040 --> 00:24:47,520
Sure.

237
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,520
But

238
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:53,080
you'll have to go release
your woman yourself.

239
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:59,560
Come on. Go ahead.

240
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:07,400
Chaiya.

241
00:25:16,960 --> 00:25:18,360
So in love.

242
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:22,600
Puna, get out of here.
Don't worry about me.

243
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:26,600
No, I can't leave you.

244
00:25:31,520 --> 00:25:34,160
Don't do this, Chaiya.

245
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:40,920
Puna.

246
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,600
The only thing I want

247
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,800
is to see you safe.

248
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:53,280
This is all I need to be happy.

249
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:57,680
Don't fail me.

250
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:01,320
Get out of here.

251
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:11,160
Go!

252
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:26,680
So in love.

253
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:29,920
Time to go!

254
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:37,400
Hurry, get out of here.

255
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:03,000
Now it's just you and me.

256
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:06,680
I've been ordered to kill you.

257
00:27:09,680 --> 00:27:12,280
Since you're willing to trade your life,

258
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:13,920
then die.

259
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:53,320
Hell's waiting for you, Chaiya!

260
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:28,760
I've gotta say you're pretty pathetic.

261
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:30,480
Chaiya!

262
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:56,840
I forgot to tell you.

263
00:28:58,600 --> 00:29:00,920
I have a backup gun.

264
00:29:04,120 --> 00:29:05,480
And more importantly,

265
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:10,080
I don't like anyone being rude
to the person I love.

266
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:18,200
You'll never get out of here.

267
00:29:19,760 --> 00:29:21,040
Yeah.

268
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:57,400
Chaiya! Chaiya!

269
00:29:57,960 --> 00:29:59,240
Chaiya!

270
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:04,920
Chaiya!

271
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:08,040
Where are you, Chaiya?

272
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,760
Don't leave me.

273
00:30:11,320 --> 00:30:14,840
Chaiya!

274
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:40,520
Chaiya!

275
00:30:51,560 --> 00:30:54,280
Hey, hug me gently.

276
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,720
I thought you were dead.

277
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:03,760
You're still alive,
so I have to hold you tight.

278
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:12,960
Alright. Hugging this tight,

279
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:15,800
I might actually die.

280
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:21,960
Oh.

281
00:31:35,800 --> 00:31:37,360
You're safe now.

282
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,800
Can you walk?

283
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:41,800
I can't.

284
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:43,880
I need help right away.

285
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:49,560
Come on. I'll help.

286
00:31:50,320 --> 00:31:52,000
Hey! Oh!

287
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:54,440
Come here.

288
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:17,040
The five-spice braised eggs
smell amazing all the way here!

289
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,600
-Oh, Teacher, you're here! Hello!
-Hello!

290
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:22,320
-Let's eat together.
-Oh, wow!

291
00:32:22,400 --> 00:32:25,440
You made so many braised eggs.
Are you feeding the whole village?

292
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:26,720
-I didn't make them.
-What?

293
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:29,080
Then who did?

294
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:31,840
I did it.

295
00:32:36,400 --> 00:32:38,000
I remembered

296
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:42,120
that this is someone's favorite dish.

297
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,840
You know me so well.

298
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:55,360
I'm feeling left out, Mom.

299
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:58,960
There's only Dad's favorite things here,
nothing for me.

300
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:01,920
Who says there isn't, dear?

301
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:07,480
Here you go.

302
00:33:13,040 --> 00:33:16,080
"The song 'Soft Heart', performed by Puna,

303
00:33:16,960 --> 00:33:19,400
nominated for Best Rising Star."

304
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:25,920
My song was nominated for an award, Dad?

305
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:29,040
Yes, dear.

306
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:32,720
Whether you win or not,

307
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:35,880
just being nominated

308
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:39,640
is already an achievement.

309
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:43,560
Thank you, Mom.

310
00:33:47,520 --> 00:33:48,800
Alright, dear.

311
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,520
From now on,

312
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:55,680
you can be the singer
you've always wanted to be.

313
00:33:58,760 --> 00:33:59,800
Yes, Dad.

314
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:05,200
Puna.

315
00:34:07,640 --> 00:34:10,800
I'm sorry, dear, for leaving you

316
00:34:12,679 --> 00:34:16,760
and even hiding things from you
when we met.

317
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:23,239
Mom, you don't have to apologize.

318
00:34:25,560 --> 00:34:27,880
I already knew everything
from Teacher Mueangphrai.

319
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:33,920
You were actually always
looking out for me,

320
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:36,360
quietly behind the scenes.

321
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:39,679
I'm the one who should be thanking you.

322
00:34:42,520 --> 00:34:44,600
About you hiding things from me,

323
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:49,280
I was never angry or upset with you.

324
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:53,280
I'm grown now.

325
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:56,679
I understand that everyone
has their reasons.

326
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:01,800
What you did had a purpose.

327
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:06,080
If you didn't love me,
you wouldn't have done it.

328
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:10,720
Puna.

329
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:13,240
Thank you, dear.

330
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:19,960
I promise.

331
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:24,120
From now on, no matter what happens,

332
00:35:25,280 --> 00:35:26,600
I will always take care of you

333
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:29,800
and protect you like this.

334
00:35:40,600 --> 00:35:44,440
I also need to apologize, Puna.

335
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:49,400
For lying to you about being Uncle Tharin.

336
00:35:52,720 --> 00:35:54,120
That's okay, Dad.

337
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:56,040
It's actually great.

338
00:35:56,120 --> 00:36:00,680
It feels like I have
both you and Uncle Tharin by my side.

339
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:02,840
Is that so, my dear?

340
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:12,040
Hey, by the way, I'm curious.

341
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:16,600
When you saw Mom
looking beautiful as before,

342
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,640
how did you feel?

343
00:36:24,160 --> 00:36:25,520
There's something

344
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:28,960
that I need to tell you, Phupha.

345
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:33,920
It's time you should know.

346
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:37,200
What is it, On?

347
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:50,840
On.

348
00:36:51,560 --> 00:36:53,880
What is this?

349
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:58,480
Am I dreaming, On?

350
00:37:00,120 --> 00:37:01,560
Your face looks the same as before.

351
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:04,960
-Yes.
-What is going on, On?

352
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,640
I'm not dreaming, am I?

353
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:11,000
Kamnan knows everything.

354
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,080
Even about us.

355
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:20,320
But he understands
and doesn't hold it against us.

356
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:23,480
The reason I followed you here
is because of this.

357
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:25,560
What do you mean?

358
00:37:25,640 --> 00:37:27,520
I want you to have plastic surgery.

359
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:28,800
Plastic surgery?

360
00:37:29,440 --> 00:37:32,200
I want to make up
for the wrongs I've done to you.

361
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:34,320
Even if it costs me everything,
I'm willing.

362
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:37,320
-Just once, On.
-Go on.

363
00:37:40,440 --> 00:37:41,560
Okay.

364
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:44,280
I'll go through with the surgery.

365
00:37:45,520 --> 00:37:46,400
Thank you.

366
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:51,320
I trust that right now,
Kamnan is finding a way

367
00:37:52,240 --> 00:37:54,120
to help us.

368
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:55,200
On!

369
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:07,000
So lately,

370
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:10,600
you've been hiding your identity
for your safety, right?

371
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:11,840
Yes.

372
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:17,160
It was all Kamnan Pong's idea.

373
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:22,840
I could hardly believe my own eyes, dear.

374
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:25,480
I thought I was dreaming.

375
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:31,760
But now I'm older,

376
00:38:32,520 --> 00:38:33,800
it won't be exactly the same.

377
00:38:34,520 --> 00:38:35,640
Hey.

378
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:37,760
Do you realize, On?

379
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:40,640
Time hasn't touched you at all.

380
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:46,400
Oh my! I'm blushing for you guys!

381
00:38:47,160 --> 00:38:51,480
The food must taste
even sweeter and better today!

382
00:38:51,560 --> 00:38:52,840
Wow.

383
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:54,440
I'm telling the truth.

384
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:56,640
Teacher, look at them flirting!

385
00:38:57,360 --> 00:39:00,160
Okay, enough. Let's eat!

386
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:03,360
Come on. Mom, sit first. Dad, sit too.

387
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:21,480
After all the hardships
we've been through,

388
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:25,680
I realize my true feelings.

389
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:29,480
What do you mean?

390
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:31,880
I know…

391
00:39:37,520 --> 00:39:39,040
when things get dangerous,

392
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:41,520
who I care about the most.

393
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:46,120
I worry about you too, Chaiya.

394
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,640
I care about you the most as well.

395
00:39:55,520 --> 00:39:56,560
But unfortunately…

396
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,320
What's wrong?

397
00:40:02,120 --> 00:40:03,200
Actually,

398
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:06,000
Deputy Chief Phuchong
gave me a new mission.

399
00:40:07,840 --> 00:40:09,760
I have to serve abroad.

400
00:40:13,200 --> 00:40:14,240
For how long?

401
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,200
Five years.

402
00:40:19,840 --> 00:40:20,960
Five years?

403
00:40:24,720 --> 00:40:25,760
Really?

404
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:29,600
Then it'll be hard
to see each other again.

405
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:35,680
Yes.

406
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:38,160
I'll have to go undercover again.

407
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:43,280
Wait for me.
I'll come back as soon as I can.

408
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:47,880
Okay.

409
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:52,360
Puna.

410
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:55,240
I'm sorry.

411
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:57,520
It's my duty.

412
00:40:58,640 --> 00:41:00,880
It's okay. I understand.

413
00:41:04,680 --> 00:41:08,240
But I don't think you really understand.

414
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:15,480
I'm exhausted, low on energy.

415
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:17,800
I just need some encouragement.

416
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:23,480
What are you talking about?

417
00:41:34,240 --> 00:41:35,600
You're not making any sense.

418
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:51,760
I'm leaving now.

419
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:13,840
You're going away for months?

420
00:42:15,040 --> 00:42:17,760
If the mission finishes early,
I might be back sooner.

421
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:19,640
But don't worry.

422
00:42:19,720 --> 00:42:22,040
I won't use any dating apps.

423
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:24,160
And I won't look at any other women.

424
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:26,400
I never said you couldn't.

425
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:28,000
Do what you want.

426
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:31,960
You're not stopping me.
Does that mean I can use dating apps?

427
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:34,960
Oops, I'm joking!

428
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:39,920
I already have you, Maria.
I'm not looking at anyone else.

429
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:43,440
Don't let me catch you, or you're dead.

430
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:46,640
Okay.

431
00:42:46,720 --> 00:42:49,880
Anyway, I'll come back quickly.

432
00:42:51,680 --> 00:42:52,920
Promise?

433
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:56,960
No. A promise should go like this.

434
00:42:58,480 --> 00:42:59,600
Hurry up!

435
00:43:00,480 --> 00:43:01,560
Promise!

436
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:04,280
Quick.

437
00:43:08,240 --> 00:43:09,440
I promise.

438
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:20,040
Good luck.

439
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:22,960
Have a safe trip.

440
00:44:06,680 --> 00:44:07,960
Mr. Sonrak.

441
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:10,480
I came to visit.

442
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:25,880
I'm sorry for treating you badly before.

443
00:44:28,040 --> 00:44:30,200
I don't hold it against you anymore.

444
00:44:39,960 --> 00:44:41,600
It's okay.

445
00:45:01,320 --> 00:45:03,640
I feel sorry for Mr. Sonrak, Teacher.

446
00:45:04,720 --> 00:45:08,480
Yeah. I didn't expect his life
to change so much because of his father.

447
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:10,760
He went from having everything

448
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:14,720
to almost everything in the house
being seized by the police as evidence.

449
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:17,560
Mr. Sonrak really had nothing to do
with the case.

450
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:21,480
No one ever knows
what the future holds, do they?

451
00:45:21,560 --> 00:45:25,200
Speaking of this, did you know

452
00:45:25,720 --> 00:45:27,800
Chaiya's completely disappeared?

453
00:45:27,880 --> 00:45:29,840
And he hasn't called you at all?

454
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:34,640
Not at all. He had to go undercover
to investigate the drug case.

455
00:45:34,720 --> 00:45:36,320
So he couldn't contact anyone.

456
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:37,680
How long has it been?

457
00:45:37,760 --> 00:45:39,880
We haven't spoken for months.

458
00:45:40,840 --> 00:45:44,240
He said he'd be on a mission abroad
for five years.

459
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:47,920
I have no idea if he's safe.

460
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:49,760
I just have a bad feeling.

461
00:45:49,840 --> 00:45:53,360
Come on. Don't overthink it.

462
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:56,080
He'll call you when he can. Trust me.

463
00:46:01,520 --> 00:46:03,240
<i>Sathu!</i>

464
00:46:03,320 --> 00:46:05,320
May Puna's love song

465
00:46:05,400 --> 00:46:08,160
move the heart
of the Savage Tiger, Chaiya,

466
00:46:08,240 --> 00:46:12,160
and bring him back. I beg you!

467
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:22,080
Hey, you! Wait!

468
00:46:30,120 --> 00:46:31,680
Our phones got switched.

469
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:24,120
You said you were going
on a five-year mission abroad.

470
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:25,840
What kind of cop are you?

471
00:47:32,360 --> 00:47:36,360
Have you forgotten? Besides being a cop,

472
00:47:36,440 --> 00:47:38,160
I'm also the Savage Tiger.

473
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:51,040
Somehow,

474
00:47:51,120 --> 00:47:53,600
the love song captured

475
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:56,640
the Savage Tiger's heart!

476
00:47:59,120 --> 00:48:01,040
Chaiya came alone?

477
00:48:01,120 --> 00:48:03,240
I shouldn't have waited for you, Manat.

478
00:48:12,400 --> 00:48:13,360
Peek-a-boo!

479
00:48:14,400 --> 00:48:15,520
Don't play around, Dad!

480
00:48:16,760 --> 00:48:19,360
Stop using that charming voice.
You're not the hero here.

481
00:48:20,000 --> 00:48:23,080
I'm not, but I have a heart
that truly loves you.

482
00:48:24,840 --> 00:48:27,680
Manat, I've missed you so much!

483
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:29,680
I missed you too.

484
00:48:36,800 --> 00:48:38,680
From now on, I'm giving you orders.

485
00:48:40,680 --> 00:48:43,040
You can't order me around.
You're not my boss!

486
00:48:43,120 --> 00:48:45,640
What if I order you

487
00:48:45,720 --> 00:48:48,680
to marry me? Can I do that?

488
00:48:51,040 --> 00:48:52,040
Of course.

489
00:48:53,280 --> 00:48:54,600
You can ask for more.

490
00:48:57,800 --> 00:48:59,280
I love you, Maria.

491
00:49:00,520 --> 00:49:02,320
I love you too, Manat.

492
00:49:35,840 --> 00:49:40,360
THE END

493
00:50:17,440 --> 00:50:21,640
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

494
00:50:21,720 --> 00:50:26,560
Then keep going like this.
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

495
00:50:26,640 --> 00:50:30,360
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

496
00:50:30,440 --> 00:50:32,120
Like no one's around, like you're alone.

497
00:50:32,200 --> 00:50:34,320
Three, two, and you two stand by here.

498
00:50:34,400 --> 00:50:36,160
Who says there isn't, dear?

499
00:50:36,240 --> 00:50:38,720
-You just sit right here.
-Once finished, switch angles.

500
00:50:39,320 --> 00:50:40,720
Cut! Let's get a different angle.

501
00:50:47,760 --> 00:50:51,640
KHOK TA YU AGRICULTURE FAIR

502
00:50:56,160 --> 00:50:57,440
Help him up.

503
00:50:57,520 --> 00:50:58,880
Then you get shocked again.

504
00:50:59,600 --> 00:51:01,520
Like this, the shock keeps coming.

505
00:51:02,120 --> 00:51:04,800
DARATHONG COUNTRY MUSIC SINGING CONTEST

506
00:51:04,880 --> 00:51:05,960
Go on.

507
00:51:07,760 --> 00:51:09,280
The moment he punches…

508
00:51:11,800 --> 00:51:13,160
Hold him down like this.

509
00:51:13,240 --> 00:51:15,760
One, two, three, done!

510
00:51:20,280 --> 00:51:21,520
It takes a lot of patience.

511
00:52:26,440 --> 00:52:29,000
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
